getNextCoordinationSphere

public CMLAtomSet getNextCoordinationSphere(java.lang.String[] atomIds)
                                     throws CMLException
expands a fragment to include immediate ligands. normally takes a ring nucleus and decorates it with the ligands but could expand to the next ligand shell of any fragment. the fragment is described by its atom ids whose ligands are determined and added to the growing atom set . this is then returned as a new molecule. It should really be renamed to "get next coordination sphere"

Parameters:
atomIds - AtomIds of nuclei
Returns:
atomSet containing nuclei and ligands
Throws:
CMLException

getNextCoordinationSphere

public CMLAtomSet getNextCoordinationSphere(CMLAtomSet atomSet)
expands a fragment to include immediate ligands. normally takes a ring nucleus and decorates it with the ligands but could expand to the next ligand shell of any fragment. the fragment is described by an AtomSet, and the ligand atoms are added to this AtomSet.

Parameters:
atomSet - AtomSet containing nuclei
Returns:
atomSet containing nuclei and ligands
